What is this?

The geoconvertor it's API JAVA created to converter coordinates using complex geodesic equation. 

Pre-requisites:

Java:
- Java Runtime Environment Version 5.0

How to install?

1) Adding geoconvertor-v0.x.jar api to the project.

2) Import
import org.geoconvertor.datum.Datum;
import org.geoconvertor.utm.GEOConvertor;

Construct an object:

GEOConvertor gcv = new GEOConvertor(); 

Call the methods:

geoToUTM(decimal_latitude, decimal_longitude, datum, central_meridian);
decToDMS(decimal_coordinate);
dmsToDec(dms_coordinate); 

More Information: http://code.google.com/p/geoconvertor/wiki/How_it_Works_eng

